E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fence"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prohibit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ban"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bar, to obstruct"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prohibit, to outlaw; to declare illegal"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to denounce, to banish, to exile; to declare an outlaw"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَظَرَ (ḥaẓara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interdiction, banning, embargo, curfew","examples":[{"text":"حَظْرُ تَجَوُّلٍ","english":"curfew"},{"text":"حَظْرُ بَيْعِ ٱلْأَسْلِحَةِ","english":"ban on the sale of arms"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ban, banning","tags":["Internet"],"examples":[{"text":"حَظْرٌ عَلَى ٱلْفَيْسْبُوك","english":"Facebook ban"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8412","headword_ar":"حَظِرٌ","root":"HZr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trees with which a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiyrap","text_ar":"حَظِيرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is made."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh thorns."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa fiY AlHaZiri","text_ar":"وَقَعَ فِى الحَظِرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aTobi","text_ar":"الرَّطْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell into that to which he was not equal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) is a prov., originating from the fact of the Arabs' collecting fresh thorns, and making of them enclosures, into which a man sometimes falls so that he becomes caught therein. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a biAlHaZiri Alr~aTobi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ بِالحَظِرِ الرَّطْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought, a large number of cattle, and of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an odious lie:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calumny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slander,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falsehood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of a calumniator, or slanderer, and liar, who kindles by his calumnies the fire of enmity, and makes it to burn up. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoqada fiY AlHaZiri Alr~aTobi","text_ar":"اَوْقَدَ فِى الحَظِرِ الرَّطْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He uttered calumny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slander:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went about with calumny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slander, and foul conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}